57:43.027 --> 57:44.526
Wow!

57:44.528 --> 57:47.563
- Only an hour late this time.
- Yeah, sorry.

57:49.099 --> 57:50.566
I get down here from New York

57:50.568 --> 57:52.701
and you can't
make it six blocks?

57:52.703 --> 57:54.136
I'm busy, come on.

57:54.138 --> 57:57.072
I can't be the first writer
to be behind on a deadline.

57:57.074 --> 57:58.874
Yeah, well, about that.

57:58.876 --> 58:00.042
What?

58:01.145 --> 58:02.878
You got a contract
for two books.

58:02.880 --> 58:04.880
We haven't seen
the second book yet.

58:04.882 --> 58:06.215
The first one wasn't that great,

58:06.217 --> 58:07.716
so what's the rush
for the next one?

58:07.718 --> 58:09.918
You've had enough extensions.

58:09.920 --> 58:13.155
Yeah, we need the manuscript
and we need it in a week.

58:13.157 --> 58:14.089
A week?

58:14.091 --> 58:17.226
That's impossible.
That's not gonna happen.

58:17.228 --> 58:20.529
Well, then we're gonna sue
you for breach of contract.

58:20.531 --> 58:21.497
What?

58:21.499 --> 58:25.267
Look, your last book
didn't work out, now did it?

58:25.269 --> 58:27.236
We need something
new from you

58:27.238 --> 58:29.905
to fill the shelves
and cover up, a stanch.

58:29.907 --> 58:33.275
And we are less likely
to play nice with you Mitch

58:33.277 --> 58:35.811
after the last debacle.

58:35.813 --> 58:36.879
I'm being serious.

58:37.681 --> 58:39.181
I made your reputation.

58:39.183 --> 58:41.550
Yeah, and we made yours.

58:41.551 --> 58:43.918
And you know, if you
could just get things to us

58:43.921 --> 58:47.256
in plenty of time so we could
edit it to our satisfaction

58:47.258 --> 58:49.825
instead of a usual trick
of bringing us things

58:49.827 --> 58:52.594
three minutes
before the deadline.

58:52.596 --> 58:56.698
Honestly, Mitch, you artistic
types, you all are the same!

58:57.701 --> 59:01.570
Plenty of ideas,
nothing to show for it.

59:01.572 --> 59:03.171
Now, what are we in
the hole for here anyways?

59:03.173 --> 59:05.040
We're selling paper

59:05.041 --> 59:07.081
and most of the business
is in e-books anyway.

59:07.778 --> 59:09.912
So, the last one
didn't go that well.

59:09.914 --> 59:11.464
We'll make it up.

59:11.465 --> 59:13.015
- Not good enough.
- I'll give you good enough.

59:13.017 --> 59:15.250
Yeah, well just give me
good enough in seven days.

59:31.302 --> 59:34.069
All right.
I'm gonna take you upstairs.

59:34.071 --> 59:36.805
Okay. What's upstairs?

59:36.807 --> 59:38.106
A surprise.

59:38.108 --> 59:40.042
- Should I close my eyes?
- No.

59:41.178 --> 59:43.946
I want to open your eyes for the
first time in our relationship.

59:43.948 --> 59:46.715
Right, there's that mysterious
writer talk again.

59:46.717 --> 59:49.217
No. No mysteries.

59:53.223 --> 59:54.256
Sophie...

59:56.760 --> 59:57.760
I love you.

59:59.129 --> 01:00:01.063
I haven't said that
to a lot of women.

01:00:02.099 --> 01:00:04.633
I want to be honest
with you about everything

01:00:06.870 --> 01:00:07.870
Come on.

01:00:11.809 --> 01:00:13.342
Shhh, shhh.

01:00:14.278 --> 01:00:15.278
Listen.

01:00:18.048 --> 01:00:19.348
I don't hear anything.

01:00:19.350 --> 01:00:22.250
It's being quiet.

01:00:22.252 --> 01:00:24.920
I've been keeping it in check
since you've been coming over.

01:00:24.922 --> 01:00:27.222
What are you hiding in there?

01:00:28.025 --> 01:00:29.025
Really?

01:00:29.860 --> 01:00:30.792
The truth.

01:00:30.794 --> 01:00:33.695
Something I've never
shown anyone before.

01:00:34.965 --> 01:00:36.365
Well, let's get this over with.

01:00:37.167 --> 01:00:38.934
I'm gonna close your eyes now.

01:00:41.739 --> 01:00:43.271
Okay.

01:00:48.879 --> 01:00:51.313
Surprise, it's me.

01:00:55.753 --> 01:00:56.785
What?

01:00:58.022 --> 01:01:00.756
That's how I get
my ideas for my stories.

01:01:00.758 --> 01:01:03.892
I defeated people
but it's how it works.

01:01:03.894 --> 01:01:05.794
I... I don't understand.

01:01:05.796 --> 01:01:07.896
It just showed up one night.
I don't know.

01:01:11.268 --> 01:01:14.136
Sophie, I do this for us.

01:01:14.138 --> 01:01:15.404
I can't... I can't do this.

01:01:16.240 --> 01:01:17.673
We let you in.

01:01:19.943 --> 01:01:21.109
Sophie!

01:01:31.855 --> 01:01:35.757
¶¶¶

01:02:01.018 --> 01:02:02.018
Hi.

01:02:03.087 --> 01:02:04.687
Hi yourself.

01:02:04.688 --> 01:02:07.128
It's the part where you ask me
if I want to have a good time?

01:02:09.326 --> 01:02:10.792
Hard to get it like it.

01:02:12.096 --> 01:02:13.228
How much?

01:02:13.230 --> 01:02:14.930
All depends on
how much you want.

01:02:14.932 --> 01:02:16.064
Fair enough.

01:02:17.868 --> 01:02:19.034
I've got money, don't worry.

01:02:19.036 --> 01:02:20.302
Who is worried?

01:02:30.881 --> 01:02:31.847
Come on.

01:02:36.253 --> 01:02:38.954
You are under arrest for
solicitation of a prostitute.

01:02:38.956 --> 01:02:40.422
This is entrapment.

01:02:40.424 --> 01:02:41.890
You asked me, big boy.

01:02:41.892 --> 01:02:43.825
You have the right
to remain silent.

01:02:43.827 --> 01:02:46.762
Anything you say maybe held
against you in the court of law.

01:02:46.764 --> 01:02:48.029
Wonderful.

01:02:49.967 --> 01:02:51.466
I love your books.

01:02:52.369 --> 01:02:54.169
Thanks. You want me to go now?

01:03:07.084 --> 01:03:11.887
¶¶¶

01:03:11.889 --> 01:03:13.388
Is he still here?

01:03:13.390 --> 01:03:15.891
- Made bail last night.
- Figures.

01:03:15.893 --> 01:03:18.260
I have been trying to get
warrant on this guy since...

01:03:19.129 --> 01:03:20.929
This may be my chance.

01:03:22.032 --> 01:03:23.749
With this in his file,

01:03:23.750 --> 01:03:25.467
someone up the chain may see
that he's not so perfect

01:03:25.469 --> 01:03:27.836
and back me up on this.

01:03:27.838 --> 01:03:28.970
Thank you.

01:03:40.117 --> 01:03:42.818
Thanks for bailing me out, man.

01:03:43.821 --> 01:03:45.461
Do we need to go
get your car now?

01:03:46.123 --> 01:03:47.422
I'll take care
of it in the morning.

01:03:47.424 --> 01:03:51.593
God, Mitch, this Sophie thing
must have you really fucked up

01:03:51.595 --> 01:03:53.128
if you're picking up hookers.

01:03:56.099 --> 01:03:59.868
I was gonna kill her
and hope nobody would notice.

01:03:59.870 --> 01:04:01.970
It's good. You should keep
that charming sense of humor,

01:04:01.972 --> 01:04:03.305
it's getting you far.

01:04:03.307 --> 01:04:05.941
I'm fucking drained.

01:04:05.943 --> 01:04:08.977
You know, I wasn't gonna say
anything but you look like shit.

01:04:08.979 --> 01:04:10.078
I was in jail.

01:04:10.080 --> 01:04:11.246
I know.

01:04:11.248 --> 01:04:13.481
And I hope you've
made a lot of friends,

01:04:13.483 --> 01:04:16.518
friends you can confide in,
talk to, you know.

01:04:18.021 --> 01:04:19.421
I feel like shit.

01:04:20.991 --> 01:04:23.024
I've been in a bad
place for a while, Nick.

01:04:23.026 --> 01:04:24.960
That's generally the reason

01:04:24.962 --> 01:04:27.362
people pick up hookers
in the first place.

01:04:27.364 --> 01:04:28.463
No, it's not that.

01:04:32.369 --> 01:04:34.302
I think I know what
I need to do now

01:04:35.505 --> 01:04:37.265
and a hooker wasn't
gonna be enough.

01:04:39.610 --> 01:04:41.443
I got some rainy day
money upstairs...

01:04:43.013 --> 01:04:44.045
to get you paid.

01:04:45.115 --> 01:04:46.214
Come with me.

01:04:58.528 --> 01:05:00.028
All right. So, I
kind of understand

01:05:00.030 --> 01:05:02.197
why you don't want people
snooping around up here.

01:05:03.033 --> 01:05:05.567
Well, I think after all
these years my secret is safe.

01:05:06.570 --> 01:05:08.236
I can't believe
I'm even up here.

01:05:08.238 --> 01:05:10.505
You've kept this whole
upstairs from me for so long.

01:05:12.910 --> 01:05:14.590
I almost don't want
to show you.

01:05:16.179 --> 01:05:17.179
Show me what?

01:05:18.649 --> 01:05:19.649
Me.

01:05:32.362 --> 01:05:33.628
I know, right?

01:05:36.466 --> 01:05:37.565
What is that?

01:05:39.069 --> 01:05:41.149
I'm trying to figure out
for years, believe me.

01:05:44.574 --> 01:05:45.674
Is it real?

01:05:45.676 --> 01:05:47.676
Yeah.

01:05:52.249 --> 01:05:53.715
Okay.

01:05:53.717 --> 01:05:55.517
All right. Uh...

01:05:57.554 --> 01:05:59.020
Thank you for showing me.

01:06:00.390 --> 01:06:04.192
I... You know, I won't say
anything to anyone about this.

01:06:05.228 --> 01:06:07.228
No, Nick, I know.

01:06:07.230 --> 01:06:08.296
No, Mitch!

01:06:08.298 --> 01:06:09.331
<i>Mitch!</i>

01:06:26.283 --> 01:06:29.317
¶¶¶

01:06:37.227 --> 01:06:42.630
¶¶¶

01:07:06.757 --> 01:07:08.023
Brilliant.

01:07:09.059 --> 01:07:10.492
Fucking brilliant.

01:07:17.567 --> 01:07:22.103
¶¶¶

01:07:41.224 --> 01:07:44.592
¶¶¶

01:08:38.482 --> 01:08:39.482
Hello?

01:08:40.350 --> 01:08:41.749
Who is there?

01:08:41.751 --> 01:08:42.751
Luke?

01:08:43.553 --> 01:08:44.652
Hello?

01:08:50.493 --> 01:08:52.127
Mitch, is that you?

01:09:00.337 --> 01:09:02.770
Shit!

01:09:02.772 --> 01:09:04.139
What's that?

01:09:06.475 --> 01:09:08.443
Okay, okay.

01:09:42.312 --> 01:09:45.813
¶¶¶

01:09:53.223 --> 01:09:55.490
Well, author Mitch Stockridge's
second novel

01:09:55.492 --> 01:09:57.559
is raking in the rave reviews.

01:09:57.561 --> 01:10:00.662
New York Times calls it
ambitious and brilliant.

01:10:00.664 --> 01:10:03.731
The Chicago Tribune
says it's a bold new step

01:10:03.733 --> 01:10:05.200
in truly self-help.

01:10:05.202 --> 01:10:07.235
<i>And the San Francisco
Chronicle says</i>

01:10:07.237 --> 01:10:09.571
<i>it's not only the most
inspirational book</i>

01:10:09.573 --> 01:10:10.638
<i>of the decade,</i>

01:10:10.640 --> 01:10:13.374
<i>it just might be the strongest.</i>

01:10:14.978 --> 01:10:19.247
¶¶¶

01:10:29.593 --> 01:10:31.326
I knew you could do it, Mitch.

01:10:31.962 --> 01:10:33.779
You're a genius.

01:10:33.780 --> 01:10:35.597
No such thing. It's a lot
of hard work and sacrifice.

01:10:35.599 --> 01:10:36.864
Matthew Lopez.

01:10:42.405 --> 01:10:44.005
Next please.

01:10:44.007 --> 01:10:46.608
To Peter Sanchez.

01:10:49.779 --> 01:10:51.479
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

01:11:06.997 --> 01:11:07.997
Mitch.

01:11:09.733 --> 01:11:11.266
Hey, Laura.

01:11:11.268 --> 01:11:13.568
I see you've got
another book out.

01:11:13.570 --> 01:11:15.536
Congratulations.

01:11:15.538 --> 01:11:18.039
- I'm sure Nick is very proud.
- Thanks. That means a lot.

01:11:18.041 --> 01:11:20.008
Have you heard
anything from Nick?

01:11:20.010 --> 01:11:21.693
No.

01:11:21.694 --> 01:11:23.377
You're his best friend.
He didn't tell you anything?

01:11:23.380 --> 01:11:24.545
I'm sorry.

01:11:24.547 --> 01:11:25.780
Please try to...

01:11:26.750 --> 01:11:27.949
I have to go, Laura.

01:11:38.962 --> 01:11:40.495
You're walking
the beat, Detective?

01:11:40.497 --> 01:11:43.564
Kind of. I was over at
Mitch Stockridge's place.

01:11:43.566 --> 01:11:46.367
Oh, funny story.
You got your warrant.

01:11:47.837 --> 01:11:49.671
Are you kidding me?

01:11:49.673 --> 01:11:52.307
I thought they were gonna
protect this guy forever.

01:11:53.543 --> 01:11:54.742
What did it?

01:11:54.744 --> 01:11:56.744
- The hooker thing?
- Yes.

01:11:56.746 --> 01:12:00.415
Well, it turns out the guy that
bailed your boy out is missing.

01:12:02.385 --> 01:12:04.686
What is it with you
and this author?

01:12:04.688 --> 01:12:05.753
I have to go.

01:12:13.863 --> 01:12:17.065
Look at this,
"ambitious and brilliant."

01:12:18.635 --> 01:12:20.501
It's the New York Times talking.

01:12:21.738 --> 01:12:22.904
You read The Chronicle yet?

01:12:24.107 --> 01:12:25.540
I got through some of them.

01:12:26.576 --> 01:12:27.842
Takes me a while these days.

01:12:30.013 --> 01:12:31.913
Advance sales are
out of the roof.

01:12:31.915 --> 01:12:33.981
It almost makes up for the time

01:12:33.983 --> 01:12:37.452
you left me alone
to go write in a cabin.

01:12:37.454 --> 01:12:38.820
You're still alive.

01:12:39.889 --> 01:12:40.889
Barely.

01:12:44.661 --> 01:12:46.894
Well, Son, you did it.

01:12:46.896 --> 01:12:50.031
- Are you being sarcastic?
- No.

01:12:50.033 --> 01:12:51.366
This time you did it.

01:12:56.106 --> 01:12:57.106
Thanks, Dad.

01:12:58.041 --> 01:12:59.107
It means the world to me.

01:13:01.811 --> 01:13:04.112
Is that what you really
all you were waiting for?

01:13:04.114 --> 01:13:05.874
You really are a mess,
aren't you?

01:13:07.684 --> 01:13:09.917
If you actually thought anything
you've done with your life

01:13:09.919 --> 01:13:11.119
was worth a damn,

01:13:11.121 --> 01:13:13.621
you wouldn't be so
worried about what I felt

01:13:14.824 --> 01:13:17.625
and you wouldn't be so angry
at the world all the time.

01:13:21.030 --> 01:13:22.063
You're right, Dad,

01:13:23.733 --> 01:13:25.500
I don't need to be
angry anymore.

01:13:48.191 --> 01:13:52.427
¶¶¶

01:13:59.803 --> 01:14:04.071
¶¶¶

01:14:19.122 --> 01:14:23.157
¶¶¶

01:14:25.128 --> 01:14:28.863
¶¶¶

01:14:29.966 --> 01:14:31.599
Get down!

01:14:34.604 --> 01:14:35.837
What?

01:14:55.124 --> 01:14:56.624
Thank you so much for the time.

01:15:00.730 --> 01:15:02.797
- Mr. Stockridge.
- Detective.

01:15:02.799 --> 01:15:04.866
It is so nice to see you again.

01:15:05.735 --> 01:15:07.235
I feel like you have
a thing for me.

01:15:07.237 --> 01:15:10.505
Mr. Stockridge, I recently
received a distraught phone call

01:15:10.507 --> 01:15:11.706
from a grieving widow.

01:15:12.542 --> 01:15:14.542
I had nothing new to tell her.

01:15:14.544 --> 01:15:16.277
She had nothing new to tell me.

01:15:16.279 --> 01:15:19.714
- Well, except for one thing.
- And what's that?

01:15:21.251 --> 01:15:23.485
Quite by chance,

01:15:23.486 --> 01:15:25.720
poor Mrs. Brennaman
corroborated Ms. Dettler's story

01:15:25.722 --> 01:15:27.755
about rooms on the second floor

01:15:27.757 --> 01:15:30.191
that no one was
allowed to go in.

01:15:30.193 --> 01:15:31.193
Hmm...

01:15:32.061 --> 01:15:33.761
I see.

01:15:33.763 --> 01:15:35.997
I see, I see, I see.

01:15:37.066 --> 01:15:40.568
- I'm a very private person.
- Mitch, I have a warrant.

01:15:40.570 --> 01:15:43.538
We can do this the easy
way or the hard way.

01:15:43.540 --> 01:15:45.640
I guess you got what you
wanted then, Detective.

01:15:46.576 --> 01:15:47.909
Will there be anything else?

01:15:47.911 --> 01:15:49.644
I need to go meet
with my publisher.

01:15:51.114 --> 01:15:53.147
If you like books,
you're welcome to join us.

01:15:53.149 --> 01:15:58.119
You know I know you never
shed any tears for Luke Rousseau

01:15:58.121 --> 01:16:02.590
and I can accept that you made
yourself not care about any

01:16:02.592 --> 01:16:04.859
or many of the others.

01:16:05.828 --> 01:16:09.730
- Nick Brennaman was your friend.
- And I miss him every day.

01:16:09.732 --> 01:16:11.666
I'll choose to believe that.

01:16:11.667 --> 01:16:13.601
I noticed you made a beeline
for the room upstairs,

01:16:13.603 --> 01:16:15.937
like you knew exactly
what you were looking for.

01:16:17.907 --> 01:16:19.073
I'm not mad.

01:16:19.075 --> 01:16:22.143
I'm just wondering
how much do you know.

01:16:22.145 --> 01:16:24.596
I know enough.

01:16:24.597 --> 01:16:27.077
Well, then you'll know no one's
going to believe your story.

01:16:29.986 --> 01:16:33.888
- You're a monster, Stockridge.
- I take your word for it.

01:16:33.890 --> 01:16:35.256
I help people.

01:16:35.258 --> 01:16:38.059
You remember the woman
from the grocery store.

01:16:38.061 --> 01:16:39.627
She said I saved
her friend's life.

01:16:39.629 --> 01:16:41.596
Even you were impressed.

01:16:41.598 --> 01:16:44.031
You think your books
help everyone, huh?

01:16:45.969 --> 01:16:48.369
Well, guess again,
they didn't help me.

01:16:48.371 --> 01:16:50.605
How? You act like I destroyed
your life or something.

01:16:50.607 --> 01:16:54.609
But you did,
Mitch the bitch.

01:16:54.611 --> 01:16:58.279
Your little stories,
inspirational stories

01:16:58.281 --> 01:17:00.915
inspired my husband
to follow his dreams

01:17:00.917 --> 01:17:02.883
and walk out on his family.

01:17:02.885 --> 01:17:04.952
So that's what
this has been about.

01:17:04.954 --> 01:17:09.890
We were happy, happy
and then you ruined everything.

01:17:09.892 --> 01:17:11.959
You'll never know how many
people I actually helped.

01:17:11.961 --> 01:17:13.628
Where is Nick, Mitch?

01:17:13.630 --> 01:17:15.680
He is not here.

01:17:15.681 --> 01:17:17.731
How could you do this
to your best friend?

01:17:17.734 --> 01:17:19.000
You're just projecting.

01:17:19.002 --> 01:17:20.522
- You're a monster.
- Leave.

01:17:21.104 --> 01:17:24.271
You're a selfish piece
of shit and I swear...

01:17:24.273 --> 01:17:26.941
I help people.
My books help people.

01:17:26.943 --> 01:17:30.111
God, keep telling yourself that.

01:17:30.113 --> 01:17:31.646
Goodbye, Detective.

01:17:41.024 --> 01:17:45.259
¶¶¶

01:18:12.088 --> 01:18:13.854
<i>Mitch Stockridge,</i>

01:18:13.856 --> 01:18:15.322
<i>his self-help books
are blowing up.</i>

01:18:15.324 --> 01:18:17.324
<i>I highly recommend...</i>

01:18:17.325 --> 01:18:19.325
<i>You should buy
Mitch Stockridge's book today.</i>

01:18:19.328 --> 01:18:22.930
<i>It's changed my life.
It can change yours.</i>

01:18:22.932 --> 01:18:25.166
Wow, Mitch, you're on time.

01:18:25.168 --> 01:18:27.001
Well, I know how you treat
authors that run late.

01:18:27.003 --> 01:18:30.237
Oh, come on, that's
water under the bridge.

01:18:30.239 --> 01:18:31.472
Would you actually have sued me?

01:18:31.474 --> 01:18:34.909
What? You gotta do
what you gotta do, Mitch,

01:18:34.911 --> 01:18:36.911
to get ahead these days.

01:18:36.913 --> 01:18:38.312
Yeah, you're right there.

01:18:38.314 --> 01:18:41.348
Can I get you something?
Coffee, biscotti?

01:18:41.350 --> 01:18:43.217
The book must be selling well.
You're being nice.

01:18:43.219 --> 01:18:46.220
Well, of course, I'm being nice.
You're back on top, Mitch.

01:18:46.222 --> 01:18:50.758
You've got everything
you ever wanted, you know.

01:18:50.760 --> 01:18:52.793
God, you must be so proud.

01:18:52.795 --> 01:18:53.795
I am.

01:18:54.764 --> 01:18:56.230
And you're fired.

01:18:57.166 --> 01:18:58.983
Excuse me?

01:18:58.984 --> 01:19:00.801
Don't take it, personal.
You know how it is.

01:19:00.803 --> 01:19:02.136
You've got to do
what you've got to do

01:19:02.138 --> 01:19:03.871
to get ahead these days.

01:19:03.873 --> 01:19:05.406
Oh, come on, Mitch.
Let's talk about...

01:19:05.408 --> 01:19:08.142
- There's nothing to talk about.
- Don't be angry.

01:19:09.479 --> 01:19:11.078
That's the funny thing.

01:19:11.080 --> 01:19:13.481
I'm not angry. I'm happy.

01:19:16.018 --> 01:19:17.151
Good luck, Natalie.

01:19:21.791 --> 01:19:22.923
Bastard.

01:19:27.964 --> 01:19:30.197
<i>We have
Author Mitch Stockridge with us</i>

01:19:30.199 --> 01:19:33.167
hot off the success
of <i> Sorry, Not Sorry.</i>

01:19:33.169 --> 01:19:35.336
- Mitch, you got a second?
- Absolutely.

01:19:35.338 --> 01:19:37.338
Glad to be here
supporting the cause.

01:19:37.340 --> 01:19:40.575
Great.

01:19:40.576 --> 01:19:43.811
We would all love to know where
do you get your ideas from?

01:19:44.847 --> 01:19:46.527
Believe it or not,
I get it a lot.

01:19:48.384 --> 01:19:50.551
Well, it's sort of like this:

01:19:50.553 --> 01:19:53.287
Ever since I was a little kid
I've been haunted by a monster

01:19:53.289 --> 01:19:56.023
and I feed it
sacrifices of people

01:19:56.025 --> 01:19:58.859
and, in return, it spits out
an outline for a best-seller

01:19:58.861 --> 01:20:01.128
and I just can't stop.

01:20:02.532 --> 01:20:03.532
Uh...

01:20:04.901 --> 01:20:09.103
Okay, well that's
why you're a writer.

01:20:09.105 --> 01:20:12.106
All right then. Wow.

